<subSubSection id="C37468B4FFBEFFDDFF10FC4C6CE93532" pageId="7" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<keyStep id="309A239AFFBEFFDDFF10FC4C6CE93ABE" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BD13B3FFFBEFFDDFF10FC4C6CE93AA3" blockId="7.[136,1452,1870,2065]" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="309F980AFFBEFFDDFF10FC4C6CE93AA3" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
1. Leaf-blade clearly differentiated from petiole, variously ovate, elliptical to orbicular; the pseudo-petiole longer than the blade; flowers always purple or purple-violet............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E40BCFFBEFFDDFB7BFC696CE93AA3" authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Swartz" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[1251,1451,1899,1920]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Heteranthera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limosa">
<emphasis id="B91AE72DFFBEFFDDFB7BFC696CE93AA3" box="[1251,1451,1899,1920]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">Heteranthera limosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD13B3FFFBEFFDDFF10FC8A6CE93ABE" blockId="7.[136,1452,1870,2065]" box="[136,1451,1928,1950]" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="309F980AFFBEFFDDFF10FC8A6CE93ABE" box="[136,1451,1928,1950]" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">- Leaf-blade not differentiated from petiole, linear; flowers purple-violet, lilac or yellow..................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="309A239AFFBEFFDDFF10FCA76CE93532" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BD13B3FFFBEFFDDFF10FCA76CE93AF4" blockId="7.[136,1452,1870,2065]" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="309F980AFFBEFFDDFF10FCA76CE93AF4" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
2. Inflorescence sessile, axillary, with a solitary flower; flowers yellow, actinomorphic; all three anthers of the same size and shape. ............................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E40BCFFBEFFDDFB75FCC06CE93AF4" authorityName="MacMillan" authorityYear="1892" baseAuthorityName="Jacquin" baseAuthorityYear="1768" box="[1261,1451,1986,2007]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Heteranthera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="B91AE72DFFBEFFDDFB75FCC06CE93AF4" box="[1261,1451,1986,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">Heteranthera dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD13B3FFFBEFFDDFF10FCDD6CE93532" blockId="7.[136,1452,1870,2065]" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="309F980AFFBEFFDDFF10FCDD6CE93532" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">
- Inflorescence pedunculate, terminal, generally with several flowers, rarely only a single one; flowers lilac, zygomorphic; anthers of different sizes and shapes........................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E40BCFFBEFFDDFB53FCF96CE93532" authorityName="Carnevali, Tapia-Munoz &amp; J. R. Grande" authorityYear="2022" box="[1227,1451,2043,2065]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Heteranthera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Commelinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yucatana">
<emphasis id="B91AE72DFFBEFFDDFB53FCF96CE93532" box="[1227,1451,2043,2065]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="27">Heteranthera yucatana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
